remarks.format:
## Remarks

`ColorExtensions` provides extension methods for converting between <xref:SkiaSharp.SKColor>, <xref:SkiaSharp.SKColorF>, and <xref:HarfBuzzSharp.HBColor>.

`SKColor` stores color as a packed `0xAARRGGBB` integer (ARGB), while `HBColor` uses a `0xBBGGRRAA` layout (BGRA). These conversions handle the byte-order difference automatically.

This class is static and does not require disposal.

## Examples

```csharp
SKColor skColor = SKColors.CornflowerBlue;
HBColor hbColor = skColor.ToHBColor();

SKColor roundTripped = hbColor.ToSKColor();
```
